  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "Много / мало / сколько + genitive",
    "explanation": "**Мно́го** (much, a lot), **ма́ло** (little, not enough), and **ско́лько** (how much) all work like **нет** — the noun that follows goes into the **genitive**: **мно́го вре́мени** (a lot of time), **ма́ло де́нег** (little money), **ско́лько са́хара?** (how much sugar?).\n\nFor now, stick to quantities of things you can't count one-by-one (time, money, bread, rice) — those use the genitive singular you already know. Counting actual items (много книг) needs a plural ending you'll get later.",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "У меня́ мно́го вре́мени сего́дня.", "en": "I have a lot of time today." },
      { "ru": "У нас ма́ло са́хара.", "en": "We have little sugar." },
      { "ru": "Ско́лько молока́ у тебя́?", "en": "How much milk do you have?" },
      { "ru": "Доста́точно хле́ба.", "en": "Enough bread." }
    ]
  },

  "vocab": [
